1.title: Robbed the Plug
1.plot: Frank promises to give Rachel a ride to her crush, er, job, but ends up on the ride of his life when a robber jumps in his car and kidnaps him at gunpoint. If only crime kingpin, U-Dead, knew that Frank wasn't in on the heist.

2.title: Ricardo D$#kwardo!
2.plot: Frank is finally ready to take down his karaoke nemesis in a microphone duel to the death. But when revenge driven U-Dead shows up for drinks, Frank is more concerned about staying alive'

3.title: Welp!
3.plot: Of course Frank's car would break down on the last ride of the day. Since one more bad review means termination, Frank calls on Chris for help, and immediately regrets it.

4.title: Welcome to the Show
4.plot: Chris gets a call that she may be the parent of a child. Is she the mom? Is she the dad? A TV show may help answer the question, but it may also push an upset Rachel into Frank's comforting arms.

5.title: Feds is Watchin'
5.plot: Chris can't stay mad at Frank and Rachel for long, well, she could, but it's kind of hard when trying to hide all of her drugs from an errant FBI raid.

6.title: Ex to the Next
6.plot:

7.title: Win Some, Lose Most
7.plot: Rachel surprises Frank with support to help him finally defeat Ricardo. The celebration is short lived when Frank accidentally surprises her with another woman.

8.title: UDead!
8.plot: If Frank wasn't so defeated, he might have paid closer attention to his most recent ride request before stopping - U-Dead and his goons!.

imdb.plot outline: Some people are born with greatness tattooed on their destiny. Others create a legacy by forging through insurmountable odds. Franklin Lee just wants to make it through the day without getting carjacked or passengers having sex in his backseat. He's failing at both. However, after a long day of driving eclectic characters around Los Angeles for his ride-share job, the silver lining for this hopeless romantic is coming home to the woman of his dreams. If only she wasn't his roommate's girlfriend. And by roommate we mean sister. Well, half-sister, does that still count? Sleeping on the couch at his sister's small apartment hasn't afforded Frank the type of privacy needed to figure out life, but it provides just enough comfort for his karaoke pursuits. His passion for the microphone has awarded Frank a reputation that embarrasses his self-esteem. As one of the most renowned songbirds in the city, Frank may discover his destiny after all, or at least a high note for his next ride.
